===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Originally {{zh-l|*𫢁}}, {{Han compound|享|京|ls=ic|nocap=yes}}, a temple and a tower – meaning "to sacrifice at a high place". During the {{w|Warring States}} period, {{lang|zh|享}} was omitted. In seal script, {{zh-l|*尤|especially; even more}} is added to the right, signifying "high; to go to a higher place".

===Etymology 1===
Cognate with {{och-l|造|id=1|to proceed to}} ({{zh-ref|Wang, 1982}}).

